Kenneth S. Ledeen is Chairman and Chief Executive Officer
of Nevo Technologies. His strategic vision is to develop and deploy systems
that meet mission-critical application needs while employing the most
advanced distributed object and internet technologies. Prior to founding
Nevo in 1997, Mr. Ledeen was a principal of Covington Associates, providing
investment banking, financial advisory, and strategic planning services
primarily to high tech and healthcare companies. He has also held senior
management positions in several leading computer engineering and software
development companies.

<p>A frequent speaker at major industry conferences,
Mr. Ledeen serves on the boards of seven technology companies. He holds
a BA from Harvard College.



